    <title>STR$ Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">string-value<sp/>=<sp/>STR$(numeric-value)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Converts a <bold>numeric value</bold> (integer or real) into its <bold>string representation</bold>.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect3 id="STR_1autotoc_md672">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>STR$(123)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>&quot;123&quot;</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>STR$(-45.67)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>&quot;-45.67&quot;</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Concatenate<sp/>number<sp/>into<sp/>a<sp/>message</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">score<sp/>=<sp/>9001</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>&quot;Score<sp/>=<sp/>&quot;<sp/>+<sp/>STR$(score)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>&quot;Score = 9001&quot;</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="STR_1autotoc_md674">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Accepts both integers and real numbers.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Result is a string in plain decimal notation (no prefixes).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Formatting (e.g. fixed decimal places) is not provided; use string operations if specific formatting is required.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
